      "content": "You can start with the Japanese, always so polite and courteous, but also kinda awkward and hesitant, like they're waiting for permission to breathe. Or the Italians, always gesticulating and dramatic, like they're trying to convince you of the importance of pasta. And don't even get me started on the Germans, always so serious and efficient, but also kinda... boring. You could also play up the stereotype of the loud, obnoxious Latin American, or the quirky, eccentric Asian-American. Just remember to keep it lighthearted and observational, and don't be afraid to poke fun at yourself.",
